## Memory Schema

Each learning is stored via `add_memories` with two parts:

**`text` parameter** (the searchable content):
The learning insight in plain text (1-3 sentences). This is what `search_memory` matches against.

**`metadata` parameter** (JSON string, write-only — not searchable):
```json
{
  "type": "pattern | pitfall | preference | architecture | tool",
  "key": "short-kebab-case-id",
  "confidence": 9,
  "source": "observed | user-stated | inferred | cross-model",
  "role": "architect | engineer | qa | product-owner | project-manager",
  "task": "task-NNN",
  "files": ["src/api.py"],
  "branch": "agent/task-041-...",
  "commit": "abc1234"
}
```

**Important**: `search_memory` cannot filter by metadata fields (Memverse constraint).
To filter by `type`, `confidence`, etc., use `list_memories` for full enumeration and
parse metadata client-side. The `metadata` field is returned by `list_memories` results.

